<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1227> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1227" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., with Eepidus for Lepidus; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. (M. Oblicius); Zon. 8.18; and on Lepidus, Polyb. 2.21.7; Liv. 23.30.15; cf. CIL 1\n     .2.617-620; see Degrassi 44f., 117, 440f. Both Consuls were sent to Sardinia, where they captured spoils which they later lost to the Corsicans (Zon. 8.18). On Publicius, see Lübker no. 4." ;
	dprr:hasID 1227 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1204> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1204" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "They built the Clivus Publicius, an aedes of Flora near the Circus Maximus, and instituted the Floralia (Varro LL 5.158; Ovid Fast. 5.275ff.; Vell. 1.14.8; Plin. NH 18.286; Tac. Ann. 2.49; Fest. 276 L). See Lübker nos. 3 and 4." ;
	dprr:hasID 1204 .
